and economic development in these two regions, State Building and Late Development draws on, and contributes to, arguments from political sociology and political economy. Based on a rigorous research design, the work offers both a finely drawn comparison of development and a compellingly argued analysis of the character and consequences of "precocious Keynesianism," the implementation of Keynesian demand-stimulus policies in largely pre-industrial economies.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mrz 2024) 4aAsian Studies. 4aPolitical Science & Political History.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Archive Pre-2000z978311053617140uhttps://doi.org/10.7591/978150171733840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501717338423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501717338/original  a978-3-11-053617-1  Cornell University Press Archive Pre-2000b2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles